---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Naledi"
  description="Engineer building local-first AI tools. Currently making data outlive the logins that produced it."
>
  <section class="container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">about</p>
    <h1>I build what should exist.</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm Naledi. I write software — mostly libraries, occasionally agents, always
        local-first when I can get away with it.
      </p>

      <p>
        The through-line across my projects is <em>making your own data useful</em>.
        Archives instead of APIs. Typed graphs instead of flat tables. Cited agent
        output instead of hallucinated summaries.
      </p>

      <p>
        I care about: personal data sovereignty, the seam between archives and
        agents, bitemporal systems, and the kind of UI that a senior engineer would
        stop scrolling for.
      </p>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/nalediym">nalediym</a></li>
        <li>RSS: <a href="/rss.xml">/rss.xml</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .about {
      padding-top: var(--sp-6);
      padding-bottom: var(--sp-9);
    }
    .about h1 {
      max-width: 20ch;
      margin-bottom: var(--sp-7);
    }
  </style>
</Base>
